Prime Minister Gordon Brown confirmed Saturday that an incident in which a blazing jeep rammed into a terminal at Scotland's Glasgow airport was `` an attack '' , as he justified raising the security threat level to `` critical '' . 
Shortly after the incident , vehicle access were closed at New Castle and Edinburgh airports on heightened state of alert , while armed police closed off Blackpool airport at the west coast of Britain . 
A burning Jeep Cherokee crashed into the main terminal building at Glasgow Airport on Saturday afternoon . 